              <h3>
               Ryan Reynolds Saturday Workout Routine = Abs &amp; Shoulders
              </h3>
              <p>
               Ryan Reynolds Saturday Workout Routine involved an Abs &amp; Shoulders workout. Start with abs, then work your way to shoulders. The Shoulder workout is the end of the week, as far as the routine goes. Make sure to work them hard, as Ryan did. Increasing mass in your shoulders is awesome, it really shows.
              </p>
              <p>
               <strong>
                Ab Circuit
               </strong>
               : 5 sets (25 reps of each)
              </p>

               <ul>
                <li>
                 <i class="fa fa-star" style="color:#333">

                  Swiss Ball Crunches
                 </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                 <i class="fa fa-star" style="color:#333">
                 </i>
                 <a href="http://youtu.be/iGhqUpHM3y4" title="Decline Body Bar Twists">
                  Decline Body Bar Twists
                 </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                 <i class="fa fa-star" style="color:#333">
                 </i>
                 <a href="http://youtu.be/x5IzwmRmXfY" title="Inchworms">
                  Inchworms
                 </a>
                 (30 secs, 10 rest, repeat once)
                </li>
                <li>
                 <i class="fa fa-star" style="color:#333">
                 </i>
                 <a href="/dumbbell-lateral-flexion-extension" target="_blank" title="Dumbbell Lateral Flexion">
                  Dumbbell Lateral Flexion / Extension

                 </a>
                </li>
               </ul>
              </div>
              <p>
               <strong>
                Shoulder Workout
               </strong>
               : 4 sets of 8-12 reps for each exercise

                </li>
               </ul>

              <h4>
               Ryan Reynolds Cardio Workout
              </h4>
              <p>
               Theres no cardio in the Ryan Reynolds workout for Blade Trinity. This is because Ryan found himself wearing away when he tried to do cardio. So, they decided to stick to ab circuits and strength training. If youre looking to get ripped, you may want to add cardio to your workout. Vary between low intensity cardio for 45 minutes and HIIT training for 15 minutes. Low intensity training, coupled with HIIT, works wonders against your fat stores.
              </p>
              <p>
               <a href="http://popworkouts.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ryan-reynolds-workout-for-blade-trinity-share.jpg">
                <img alt="ryan-reynolds-workout-for-blade-trinity-share" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10015" height="400" src="http://popworkouts.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ryan-reynolds-workout-for-blade-trinity-share.jpg" title="ryan-reynolds-workout-for-blade-trinity-share" width="318"/>
               </a>
              </p>
              <h2>
               Ryan Reynolds Diet For Blade Trinity
              </h2>
              <p>
               The Ryan Reynolds diet for Blade Trinity was quite an adventure. He was used to eating whatever he wanted.
               <a href="http://www.mensfitness.com/training/build-muscle/ryan-reynolds-superhero-workout" target="_blank" title="According to Men's Fitness Ryan Reynolds Superhero">
                According to Mens Fitness
               </a>
               , the Blade Trinity Diet was a 3,200 calorie diet that helped Ryan Reynolds gain 25 pounds for the role. To get there, Ryan Reynolds had to make some big changes and discoveries. He says:
              </p>
              <blockquote>
               <p>
                I learned that 80% of building muscle is diet. We got the food down to a science, making sure I was getting enough calories to gain mass, but not fat. A lot of oatmeal, eggs, protein bars for snacks, chicken, fish or steak for dinner. I ate a lot of small meals all day long. Lots of protein, but plenty of carbs, too. I really dont believe in that no-carb stuff. Its probably not good for youand it makes you pretty cranky.
               </p>
              </blockquote>
              <p>
               The Ryan Reynolds diet for Blade Trinity includes:
              </p>
              <ul>
               <li>
                <strong>
                 Breakfast
                </strong>
                : 2-4 Eggs scrambled, 2-4 cups of Steel-cut Oatmeal mixed berries, apple sauce (watch the sugar content), cinnamon, and a serving of almond butter (as a good fat, remember that fat is crucial in testosterone production needed for bigger muscles), more egg whites if Ryans appetite was high.
               </li>
               <li>
                2 hours later: protein bar 12-20g of protein
               </li>
               <li>
                <strong>
                 Lunch
                </strong>
                : All sorts of Veggies, Brown rice, Fish or Chicken / Ahi Tuna with dark, leafy green salad with oil and balsamic/cider vinegar.
               </li>
               <li>
                2-3 hours later: Pre-workout Protein bar or preferably shake
               </li>
               <li>
                <strong>
                 Dinner
                </strong>
                : Similar to lunch, (Lean Protein and Lots of Vegetables), substitute a different lean protein to add variety to the diet. Light Oil &amp; Balsamic dressing on a dark, leafy green salad.
               </li>
               <li>
                2 hours later: Optimum Whey Protein Shake before bed (throughout the night if he really was going through a bulking phase).
               </li>
              </ul>
              <p>
               Ryan Reynolds says that for his diet for Blade Trinity:
              </p>
              <blockquote>
               <p>
                I ate something pretty much every 2-3 hours, never stuffing myself, but never letting myself get hungry.. As well as drinking plenty of water throughout the day.
               </p>
              </blockquote>
              <p>
               His nutritionist, Bobby Strom says:
              </p>
              <blockquote>
               <p>
                Your body doesnt need to store fat for energy if youre feeding it all the time.
               </p>
              </blockquote>
              <p>
               This is why the Ryan Reynolds for diet for Blade Trinity included him eating every 2-3 hours. You want to be a little bit hungry between meals, and should eat healthy snacks. Eat apples for fiber, and nuts like almonds, or other healthy fat sources.
              </p>
              <blockquote>
               <p>
                While eating a protein/carb mix every 2 hours all day, Id wind up having about 8  10 tiny meals instead of 3 big meals over the course of a day. No carbs at night, but plenty during the day. This kind of diet kept my blood sugar even and gave me the requisite energy needed for the physicality of the role.
               </p>
              </blockquote>
              <p>
               Its important not to stuff yourself, either. An even intake of food throughout the day will keep your metabolisms engine going. Protein supplements can be swapped out for BCAAs if you prefer not to drink milk.
              </p>
              <p>
               <a href="http://popworkouts.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ryan-reynolds-abs-blade-trinity-workout.jpg">
                <img alt="ryan-reynolds-blade-trinity-diet-abs" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10009" height="269" src="http://popworkouts.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ryan-reynolds-abs-blade-trinity-workout.jpg" title="ryan-reynolds-blade-trinity-diet-abs" width="164"/>
               </a>
              </p>
              <p>
               Meals were cooked once or twice a week to save time. More importantly, cooking in advance makes sure that you dont start reaching into the fridge for things youre not supposed to eat. If you dont feel like cooking, its easy to make up an excuse and grab the wrong thing. Blade Trinity co-star, Dominic Purcell, says about the Blade Trinity diet:
              </p>
              <blockquote>
               <p>
                Were on this very high intensive protein, complex carbohydrate diet. Getting up in the morning and having oatmeal, then a protein shake. And then eating 2 hours later. I mean, Im having meals every 2 hours. Im topping tuna with vegetables then chicken breast with lettuce, and then protein barsGive Me A Pizza!
               </p>
              </blockquote>
              <p>
               Jessica Biel says:
              </p>
              <blockquote>
               <p>
                Its all about the diet and the exercise. I really have discovered. Eating 2-3 big meals per daynot good. Your metabolism is slowerIn a perfect world, have 6-8 small meals a day.
               </p>
              </blockquote>
              <p>
               Talking about steel-cut oatmeal, their trainer says:
              </p>
              <blockquote>
               <p>
                It may sound a little boring, but its very good complex carbohydrate, which is really low in fat. Id put fresh fruit in it, usually berries like blueberries. Then I add a little bit of almond milk to sweeten it and a bit of protein powder, so they got some carbohydrates and protein in one meal. I also added some flax seeds, which are essential fats.
               </p>
              </blockquote>
              <p>
               For lunch, Ryan Reynolds would stick to a clean protein. His nutritionist says:
              </p>
              <blockquote>
               <p>
                I served a clean protein, like chicken breast or Ahi tuna, not the canned stuff. Sometimes Id give them flank steak, which is a really lean red meat. Then Id put an oil and [balsamic] vinegar dressing on the salad. Vegetables are carbohydrates that you can eat in bulk. You could eat a lot of grilled vegetables.
               </p>
              </blockquote>
              <p>
               Ryan Reynolds dinners usually looked a lot like his lunches, only with a different selection of lean meats and vegetables. In sum, the Ryan Reynolds diet included:
              </p>
              <ul>
               <li>
                steel-cut oatmeal(They used McCanns Steel Cut Oatmeal-takes 1/2 to cook so you know its good)
               </li>
               <li>
                Hate Almond Butter? Eat flax seeds or avocado (as a substitute for almond butter, both healthy fats, flax seeds have to be ground in a coffee grinder prior to eating for actual benefit.)
               </li>
               <li>
                (Quest is a good brand) protein bars
               </li>
               <li>
                fresh fruit, like blueberries with the oatmeal (Find ways to make it taste good without sugar)
               </li>
               <li>
                2 eggs, slice of avocado (quick breakfast, especially if you find the recipe to bake this combination in the oven the night before)
               </li>
               <li>
                all sorts of vegetables (Reynolds really did eat ALL sorts)
               </li>
               <li>
                sweet potatoes (great carbohydrate with slow-release energy)
               </li>
               <li>
                chicken breast (staple of most bodybuilding diets)
               </li>
               <li>
                Ahi tuna (only sear for about 1-1.5 minute per side)
               </li>
               <li>
                protein shakes (whey and water mixed together, not the sugary brand types)
               </li>
               <li>
                apple and almonds as a great snack (great snacks combine protein, carbs, and healthy fats)
               </li>
               <li>
                brown rice (slow releasing energy with magnesium as an added bonus for muscle building)
               </li>
               <li>
                flank steak (get grass-fed beef or bison if you can, Trader Joes is a good place to locate such a product, unless you actually know a local farmer)
               </li>
               <li>
                Reynolds also never ate carbs after 8:00pm, only protein shakes.
               </li>
              </ul>
              <p>
               Ryan Reynolds says:
              </p>
              <blockquote>
               <p>
                I attribute my results mostly to nutrition. Never do any of that carb-starve crap. I was completely floored by the 3 months of trainingI gained 15 pounds of muscle, while dropping to 3% body fat. I attribute most of my results to nutrition.
               </p>
              </blockquote>
              <p>
              </p>
              <h3>
               Ryan Reynolds Workout Supplements

              <p>

              </p>

                I gained a lot more muscle mass when I went on creatine.
               </p>

              <h3>
               Ryan Reynolds Workout For Blade Trinity Tips
              </h3>
              <p>
               Ryan Reynolds Workout For Blade Trinity Tips include:
              </p>
              <p>
               Ryan Reynolds says diet is the most important part of the training for Blade Trinity:
              </p>
              <blockquote>
               <p>
                The main thing I learned about this whole process is how important food is. Transforming your body quickly is a genetic ability, but can also be traumatic. Eating properly is 80% of the equation. Most people think its the other way around
               </p>
              </blockquote>
              <p>
               Also, slow and steady wins the race. Do a workout youre happy doing, but that challenges you. The advantage that actors have when theyre doing these workouts is that they have a top trainer, theyre getting paid to be in shape, and they have no choice but to do it. The disadvantage they have is that theres no real reason to keep it up, once the movies done.
              </p>
              <blockquote>
               <p>
                When asked on whether hes maintained his physique: No way! It was nice to be able to take a break. But just as Id gotten used to being lazy again and sitting on my ass all day, we had to re-shoot some scenes, so they sent me back into the gym. Im glad, though, because I ended up finding this nice gray area, where I still work out four or five times a week and enjoy it, but its not to that extreme level.
               </p>
              </blockquote>
              <p>
               The advantage we all have is that we can visualize our goals, take our time, and have fun. The more fun you have with this workout, the better. But, that doesnt mean you will get results from doing very little. Motivate yourself to push through the Ryan Reynolds workout for Blade Trinity.
              </p>

                 <img alt=":(" class="wp-smiley" src="http://3-ps.googleusercontent.com/hk/0UpSEl-hBq7LiQL4Czt3imO9k3/www.popworkouts.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/frownie.png.pagespeed.ce.oGiEY4az8jrHhEYib-fC.png" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;"/>

               <li class="comment " id="li-comment-48074">
                <article>
                 <footer>
                  <img alt="Chris Davis" class="avatar avatar-50 photo" height="50" src="http://3-ps.googleusercontent.com/hk/0UpSEl-hBq7LiQL4Czt3imO9k3/www.popworkouts.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/50x50xChris-Davis_avatar_1427222067-50x50.jpg.pagespeed.ic.Vq8ItjBdiGldGG8rEacz.jpg" width="50"/>
                  <cite>

                  <a class="comment-link" href="#li-comment-48074">
                   <time pubdate="1398399240">
                    Apr 24, 2014 at 9:14 pm
                   </time>
                  </a>
                 </footer>
                 <div class="comment-content">
                  <p>
                   The best way to split would be to either skip the Saturday workout entirely, or incorporate some of those exercises into your Friday workout. Ryan Reynolds really wanted his shoulders popping for Blade Trinity, so he worked them 2x per week.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                   For the strength training, do all 4 sets of the same exercise, then move onto the next. The exception is if there is a superset. There, you do two exercises back-to-back. Then, proceed to the next exercise.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                   The benefit of strength training this way is building muscle. Youre trying to completely tire out the muscle. If you were to do circuit training, jumping from one set of each exercise to the next, that would be more of a fat burning workout. Circuit training is typically used when youre doing a full-body routine.
                  </p>
                 </div>

                  <p>

                <p>

                   <time pubdate="1419421568">

                   </time>
                  </a>
                 </footer>
                 <div class="comment-content">
                  <p>
                   Ryan Reynoldss goals may be different from yours. For Blade Trinity, he was more concerned with looking cut, than getting bigger. Go ahead and pyramid your sets if your primary goal is to get bigger. Yes, he stuck to the same weight each set.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                   If youre focused on getting cut, then the 8-12 rep range is ideal. Yes, if you can do 12 reps then you should be increasing the weight. Reynolds would aim for a weight that he could do 12 times the first set, then try get get as many as possible (at least 8) each additional set.
                  </p>
                 </div>
